Do’s
Think before you post — ensure your content is appropriate and respectful.
Maintain privacy — review and adjust your account privacy settings regularly.
Be professional — remember future employers may view your profiles.
Verify information before sharing to avoid spreading misinformation.
Respect others — communicate politely and avoid offensive language.


Don’ts
Don’t share personal or sensitive information (e.g., address, passwords).
Don’t engage in online arguments or harmful discussions.
Don’t post inappropriate photos, videos, or comments.
Don’t plagiarize or use others’ content without credit.
Don’t overshare — keep a healthy boundary between personal and public life.
